FBIS4-24236 "drafr124_a_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda President's Widow Denies RPF Involved President's Widow Denies RPF Involved LD2706222394 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 1800 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706222394 Paris France-2 Television Network French BFN [Excerpts] Hatred broke out in Rwanda and atrocious massacres took place because of an attack on the plane carrying the presidents of Rwanda and Burundi in Kigali on 6 April. [passage omitted] A former officer [Captain Barril] is reported to have got hold of the black box in Kigali, where he went at the request of the family, who have found refuge in France, so that he could start all inquiries he deemed useful to find the truth about the attack: [Begin recording] [Mrs. Habyarimana, Rwandan president's widow] You know, inquiries have been started, but I can tell you that people said straight away that the RPF [Rwanda Patriotic Front] was behind the attack but, since I left the country without knowing what people were saying, I can guarantee that the Rwandan army did not shoot at the president because the Rwandan army did not have any missiles. [end processing] [passage omitted] The Dassault-Aviation company has just issued a clarification that goes against Captain Barril's revelations: According to Dassault-Aviation, there was no black box on the former Rwandan president's plane, a Falcon-50.
